<subSubSection pageId="24" pageNumber="23" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="24.[192,1439,1182,1238]" pageId="24" pageNumber="23">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,347,1182,1206]" pageId="24" pageNumber="23">Etymology.</emphasis>
This species is named for the Tilarán mountain range in 
<collectingCountry box="[1027,1159,1182,1206]" name="Costa Rica" pageId="24" pageNumber="23">Costa Rica</collectingCountry>
, where the Monteverde locality is located.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="24" pageNumber="23" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="24.[192,1440,1261,1382]" pageId="24" pageNumber="23">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,335,1261,1285]" pageId="24" pageNumber="23">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
This species is distinguished from other 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Jacoby" authorityYear="1881" box="[861,934,1262,1286]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Beltia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[861,934,1262,1286]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="23">Beltia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the combination of a uniform bright metallic green head, prothorax, and elytra, with legs, pterothorax, and abdomen orangish brown. In all other metallic green 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Jacoby" authorityYear="1881" box="[449,522,1326,1350]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Beltia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="24" pageNumber="23" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[449,522,1326,1350]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="23">Beltia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the thorax and at least the base of the abdomen are the same color as the dorsal side.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="24" pageNumber="23" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="24.[192,1440,1406,1463]" pageId="24" pageNumber="23">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,323,1406,1430]" pageId="24" pageNumber="23">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species has been collected only from Monteverde and surrounding localities in the Tilarán mountain range of 
<collectingCountry box="[524,655,1439,1463]" name="Costa Rica" pageId="24" pageNumber="23">Costa Rica</collectingCountry>
(
<figureCitation box="[671,759,1439,1463]" captionStart="Figures 80–82" captionStartId="44.[192,286,1848,1870]" captionTargetBox="[203,1427,215,1809]" captionTargetId="figure@44.[203,1429,211,1815]" captionTargetPageId="44" captionText="Figures 80–82. Distribution maps for Beltia spp.: Nicaragua, Costa Rica, and Panama. 80) Beltia angustomarginata (squares), B. osa (triangles), B. vacilona (circles). 81) Beltia chiriquensis (circles), B. herreri (stars), B. nicaraguensis (hexagons). 82) Beltia sanchezae (square), B. tilarana (inverted triangles), B. tisingalita (stars)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3713529" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3713529/files/figure.png" pageId="24" pageNumber="23">Fig. 82</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
